(1, 'Mindfulness meditation', 'Méditation de pleine conscience', '<div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<strong>Topic of the workshop&nbsp;: </strong>Illness and stress</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<strong>8 week session</strong><br />\r\n		Start: Friday, February 17 2012<br />\r\n		<strong>Day: </strong>Friday<br />\r\n		<strong>Time: </strong>7:30 p.m.<br />\r\n		<strong>Session time: </strong>1:30<br />\r\n		<strong>Language:</strong> Bilingual or as participants<br />\r\n		Cost: $ 250 including taxes (payable in one payment at registration)<br />\r\n		<strong>Inscription&nbsp;: </strong>514-939-6360</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		Mindfulness Meditation Training for Stress Reduction caused by Illness.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		Illness is often accompanied by a certain amount of stress and anxiety. This is true of physical as well as emotional illnesses. Sometimes this stress could cause us more suffering than the actual illness itself.</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		Mindfulness Meditation Training helps us to be in touch with our feelings, to distinguish them from our thoughts, and to find peace in the present moment rather than lose ourselves in anxiety for the future. This training is essential for being able to relax in difficult situations, and for being able to find a smile.</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		Each evening will include short talks, guided meditations or a body scan, mindfulness training, walking meditation or a short T&rsquo;ai Chi warmup, sharing, and occasionally, meditation with music.</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<strong>Joseph Emet, Mindfulness Meditation&nbsp;</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>', '<div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<strong>Th&egrave;me&nbsp;de l&rsquo;atelier : </strong>La maladie et le stress</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<strong>Session de 8 semaines</strong><br />\r\n		<strong>D&eacute;but:</strong> vendredi 17 f&eacute;vrier 2012<br />\r\n		<strong>Jour&nbsp;:</strong> les vendredis<br />\r\n		<strong>Heure:</strong> 19h30<br />\r\n		<strong>Dur&eacute;e d&rsquo;une session&nbsp;:</strong> 1h30<br />\r\n		<strong>Langue:</strong> bilingue ou selon les participants<br />\r\n		Co&ucirc;t: 250 $ taxes incluses (payable en un seul paiement &agrave; l&#39;inscription)&nbsp;<br />\r\n		<strong>Inscription&nbsp;</strong>: 514-939-6360</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		Entrainement &agrave; la pleine conscience pour r&eacute;duire le stress qui accompagne la maladie.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		Quelle que soit la cause d&rsquo;une maladie (physique ou &eacute;motionnelle), elle est souvent accompagn&eacute;e d&rsquo;une part d&rsquo;anxi&eacute;t&eacute; ou d&rsquo;un stress important. Dans certains cas, ce stress pourrait nous incommoder m&ecirc;me plus que la maladie elle-m&ecirc;me.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		L&rsquo;entrainement &agrave; la pleine conscience nous aide &agrave; entrer en contact avec nos sensations et &agrave; reconnaitre nos pens&eacute;es. La pleine conscience nous aide &agrave; retrouver la paix du moment pr&eacute;sent au lieu de nous perdre dans une projection anxiog&egrave;ne du futur. Cet entrainement est essentiel pour apprendre &agrave; relaxer dans des circonstances difficiles, et pour retrouver le sourire.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		Chaque soir&eacute;e comprendra des courtes causeries, des m&eacute;ditations guid&eacute;es ou un &laquo; body scan &raquo;, des entrainements &agrave; la pratique de la pleine conscience, la marche m&eacute;ditative ou un r&eacute;chauffement de style Tai Chi, des p&eacute;riodes de partage, et parfois une m&eacute;ditation avec musique.&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		&nbsp;</div>\r\n	<div>\r\n		<strong>Joseph Emet, m&eacute;ditation de pleine conscience</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>', '2011-11-26');
